description:
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to apply for the exciting opportunity to become the Deputy Director and Head of Portfolio on a 12 month secondment basis. The Deputy Director and Portfolio Lead for Mental Health, Learning Disability &amp; Autism is a pivotal member of the Directorate of Education &amp; Quality (DEQ) senior leadership team as well as the senior lead for the delivery of HEE’s Mental Health Portfolio of work in support of achieving the ambitions set out in the LTP Mental Health Implementation Plan 2019/20 – 2023/24 and NHS People Plan. This Portfolio consists of the above mentioned three programmes of work which encompasses a significant number of projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will act as a role model in terms of HEE’s values and behaviours and will support the SRO and Executive Sponsors to foster a collaborative, supportive, inclusive Portfolio Team environment for delivery of this complex large-scale education and training Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will be required to have excellent communication skills and to collaborate and influence NHS stakeholders across the field of mental health services. You will be required to demonstrate strong leadership and have strategic development skills to drive forward this large scale change programme, you will be adept at leading large scale programmes for effective national implementation, delivery and roll out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note there will be an assessment held immediately before the interview for this Post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are offered at any HEE office, however remote working will be the default position during the current COVID 19 Pandemic. This will be continually reviewed in line with HEE policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role will be offered to applicants on a secondment basis only, agreement should be obtained from their employer prior to submitting the application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 9 with a full-time starting salary of £91,004, with a pay step increase after 5 years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For posts based in Inner London, the above salaries will include the additional supplement of 20% of basic salary, subject to a minimum payment of £4,473 per annum and a maximum payment of £6,890 per annum. This is offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and is based on office location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close the advert early once a sufficient number of applications have been received.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ria Corey, Head of GLP Delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Ria.corey@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 07920 834876&lt;/p&gt;
